thin the family Fabaceae and the genus Lotus. It is native to the southwestern United States and northern Mexico. The species is a perennial aquatic plant that grows in shallow water. Lotus nevadensis is often found in slow-moving streams, rivers, and lakes. It is a member of the Lotus genus, which consists of various aquatic and terrestrial plant species.", "benefits": "Lotus nevadensis has been traditionally used in herbal medicine to treat various health issues. Its extracts have been reported to exhibit antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial properties. Research suggests that the plant may have potential in reducing oxidative stress and inflammation in the body. Additionally, Lotus nevadensis is believed to have cardio-protective effects and may help regulate blood sugar levels. Further studies are needed to confirm the full scope of its health benefits.", "parts": "Lotus nevadensis, primarily the roots and rhizomes, are used in traditional medicine for various purposes. The roots are believed to have anti-inflammatory properties and are used to treat digestive issues. The plant's roots and rhizomes are also used in some cultures to treat fever and skin conditions. However, more research is needed to confirm the effectiveness of these uses. In addition, the plant's parts are also used in some traditional remedies to treat respiratory issues."}